{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Mushroom Duxelle","content":["Place portobello mushrooms, porcini mushrooms, shallots, butter and garlic in mixing bowl then chop  <nobr>5 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then sauté <nobr>3 min\/100°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add Madeira, thyme, salt and pepper then, without measuring cup, sauté <nobr>40-50 min\/90°C\/\/speed 1<\/nobr> until mixture has become a dry paste and most of the liquid has evaporated. Transfer to a bowl and place in fridge until needed (see tip)."]},{"title":"Beef Wellingtons","content":["Place butter, flour, water and salt in mixing bowl then mix <nobr>20 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr>. Tip dough out, shape into a ball then wrap in cling film and place in fridge for 20 minutes. Meanwhile, clean mixing bowl and continue with recipe.","In a large frying pan, heat oil over a high heat until very hot. Place steaks in pan, 2 at a time, and sear for 20 seconds on each side. Transfer to a large plate to cool. Once steaks are cool, season well with salt and pepper.","On a lightly-floured surface, roll out chilled dough to a long rectangle (approx. 60 cm x 20 cm). Fold bottom third up to cover middle third then fold top third down over this. Seal edges then give dough a quarter turn so that the fold is on the left. Repeat rolling and folding process twice more.","Divide pastry into 4 equal-sized pieces and, on a lightly-floured surface, roll each one out to a square (approx. 20 cm). If necessary, trim edges to form a neat square.","Brush each pastry square with beaten egg. Place ⅛ duxelle mixture in centre of one pastry square, then place a steak on top. Top steak with another ⅛ duxelle mixture.","Bring 2 opposite corners of pastry up over the steak to overlap in the centre, tucking in the sides to make a neat parcel. Brush with beaten egg, then bring remaining 2 corners to the middle to overlap each other. Turn parcel over, brush all over with beaten egg then lightly score the top twice with a sharp knife. Repeat until all pastry is used.","Carefully transfer parcels to a greased baking tray and chill for 30 minutes. Meanwhile, preheat oven to 220°C and make red wine jus."]},{"title":"Red Wine Jus","content":["Place shallots, garlic and thyme in mixing bowl then chop <nobr>2 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add butter and, without measuring cup, cook <nobr>4 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add port, red wine, beef stock, balsamic vinegar and sugar then, with simmering basket in place of measuring cup, cook <nobr>14-16 min\/Varoma\/speed 3<\/nobr> until sauce reaches desired consistency.","Pass through a fine sieve into a saucepan, season to taste then keep warm."]},{"title":"Cooking","content":["Cook beef Wellingtons on a high shelf in the oven for 20 minutes (220°C) (rare), 25 minutes (medium-rare) or 30 minutes (medium-well). Serve immediately, accompanied by red wine jus and vegetables of choice."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Mushroom Duxelle","content":["225 g fresh portobello mushrooms, quartered","10 g dried porcini mushrooms, soaked in boiling water for 15 minutes then drained and squeezed of excess water","50 g shallots, halved","30 g unsalted butter, diced","1 garlic clove","50 g Madeira wine","2 sprigs fresh thyme, leaves only","1 pinch fine sea salt","1 pinch ground black pepper"]},{"title":"Beef Wellingtons","content":["200 g unsalted butter, diced (2 cm), then frozen for 1 hour","200 g plain flour, plus extra for dusting","90 g water, cold","½ tsp fine sea salt, plus extra for seasoning","groundnut oil, for searing, plus extra for greasing","4 beef fillet steaks, (180-200 g each, 3-4 cm thick)","ground black pepper, for seasoning","2 large eggs, beaten"]},{"title":"Red Wine Jus","content":["50 g shallots, halved","1 garlic clove,","1 sprig fresh thyme, leaves only","50 g salted butter, diced","100 g port,","150 g red wine","100 g beef stock, hot","20 g balsamic vinegar,","35 g dark brown 